Photon is a fully controlled Light System with constant LED lighting.   The advanced Modular Studio allows instant Light Scenes change, controllable via Smartphone or PC. Modular easy-to-install system enables you to shoot different size objects, miniature or massive. FEATURES 
Each module consists of 25 active light blocks 4x4 inches 
Each block has 36 LED elements  
Total 2700 LED lights  
Module size: 20x20 inches 
Each module has its Wi-Fi transmitter 
ADVANTAGESSimple installationDoes not require any professional skillsPriceMuch cheaper than studio equipmentPlacing, space savings  1/4 sq.m  in contrast to 3 sq.mSpeedInstant change of lightingVisibilityWhen lighting is constant on the object, you instantly see the result of lighting sceneSkillsAt home, in the office or shop settings you can easily produce quality content without any dedicated photography skills.  
   1. Fully controlled Lighting System with instant change of Light ScenesWe do not relocate the light source, but we shift the light. The object is illuminated from many different angles using the optimally arranged LEDs in each module.It's all about the control over the light! 2. Auto ModeShoot & Upload HQ visuals just in seconds. We created a sophisticated library of various light scenes. Enjoy results right away with 10-15 ready-to-use light scenes. 3. Saving Light ScenesSet up your own scenes and save them for later use or just download free pre-sets. Take control of every flare! 4. 
Choose various ways how to install modules: from 1 up to 20 blocks.Don't need a cube? - Build a wall with no sides!Want to have more light from the top? - No problem - just set it! 5. Ready-to-use solutionStraight out of the box. Get the set and immediately shoot. Modify your module system with add-ons to achieve spectacular output. 6. Shoot like a PROPre-sets provide impressive results without any dedicated photography skills. See how the object will look on a screen & rapidly adjust the light scene to get the most out of it. Put a Pro to work for You!  Modules configuration is changed according to shooting object size, backgrounds and screens necessity. The system also allows connecting more than 3 modules: 1 Module 2 Modules 3 Modules The module system was invented and configured to shoot objects and compositions of virtually any size.   https://apps.apple.com/ua/app/photonlms/id1447167914?l=enBeing assembled and connected to power supply, modules run test mode (turn all on) to check serviceability and welcome command (smile) to add a photo. Each module then connects to Wi-Fi, which is indicated in the App. After that you can easily manage modules from any device that's in the same net. Modules control is managed through display of light scenes on the device screen, (Smartphone) by setting up your scenes or downloading pre-sets.The Photon LMS App changes light scene instantly from any device: tablet, smartphone or laptop. Lightweight and easy to use an app for those who appreciate Time, Speed & Quality. The App comes with a generous introductory package of FREE pre-sets. It is simple and straightforward to use, designed to pursue top efficiency. Everything is streamlined and simplified for your convenience!To find out more about Photon LMS products, please, visit photonlms.com    1. Price Costs less than a set of flashes. Literally. The whole studio will cost you way less than a set of ordinary flashes and accessories.2. Size One easy-to-use photo studio instead of loads of equipment:when shooting small objects, the standard equipment is too large and bulky one. Moreover, the process also requires constant control and appropriate light settings adjustments.3. Skills  Take professional photos at home, in the office or shop!You don't need to have a wide knowledge of lighting settings or any photography skills to obtain a perfect result.4. Time Imagine you have an ONLINE shoe shop with a constantly changing product line. You'd highly likely require regular influxes of new, High-Quality content. You ask a photographer to take photos, which (objects packing ->  take to the photographer ->  shoot - edit ->  get objects ->  receive content) is definitely a TIME & MONEY consuming process. Photon LMS is straight out of the box, ready to use solution for e-commerce entrepreneurs to create in-house product photos!5. Portability Strong & Light materials to handle!To maintain the portable concept, we will use strong and light materials to make it easy to carry neatly.   We know how to build a Light Box people would love to use!Photon - is it really worth it? - Definitely!You save Space, Time & Money. You get Quality, Speed & Visibility.  We do the work of photographer faster, better and more convenient by saving his Time & Money!  Gallery of Hight-Quality Photos LET'S MAKE A BRIGHT FUTURE FOR PRODUCT PHOTOGRAPHERS!  New generation of LightBox!Photon prototype basic electronics r.003 specification: 
LED Manufacturer - CREE; 
LED Package (mm) - 2835; 
LED Colour temperature - 5600K; 
LED CRI > 95%;
Light pulsations level < 5%, frequency - 400-800 kHz; 
Illuminance on the bottom of Photon box - 25000 lux; 
1 Module input DC voltage - 24 V; 
1 Module maximum input current - 3.4 A; 
Maximum Power Consumption (All cells at maximum brightness) 
100 W per module & 300 W per basic kit (3 modules);
One cell power consumption - 3-3.3 W  
 The MONSTER POWER lighting to draw any light scene you may need to cover objects. Energy-efficient LEDs are built-in in every module.    We have come a long way since we first came up with the idea of creating a fully controlled light system one year ago. We believed that the advanced modular studio can change the way we take photos at home.With this in mind, our team spent countless nights designing, prototyping, testing, programming, and pitching our ideas to thousands of people, receiving feedback on Photon LMS. Six months in, our product has been verified and is ready for manufacturing.   WE MUST BEGIN:
 "At first there was an IDEA! The birth of it was quite simple: for the umpteenth time when I faced problems of object shooting, I figured out that all currently available equipment is inconvenient, non-practical and not technological (flashes, softboxes, fixations,etc.), how bulky it is, and the main issue - how EXPENSIVE is all of that is combined!Then I've decided to purchase standard photo boxes for detailed object shooting, however, I also found disadvantages in them: mostly made for isolated objects on the background, it was still difficult to cope with the light. That's how I got the concept of a controlled light system.Afterward, I made 3D modeling design of the photo studio, pinned my idea in away.Since that moment I can proudly state that it was the beginning of our StartUp! I have started testing: proofing my theory, I bought LED lamps and black cardboard â€” created the first prototype by myself. Using this first sample of Photon LMS I've undergone the detailed object shooting for our partners. Everything worked out just right!Thus we decided to continue working on the first prototype. In a short while, it was ready, made of plywood & metal. The software was managed exclusively on one old tablet, nevertheless, it worked!In August 2018 we went public with that achievement and won Concepter Acceleration program as well as CES2019 booth supported by UVCA. It was a huge success! Though the real complex part was only impending, we were to create a fully operating prototype and all we had was 2 months to figure all of that out. We got to work with all our strength. There were numerous tests with LED, frame details, mounting systems, electronics schemes, and software. Thankfully, we made it! Before our pitch at CES2019 we have already had a fully working prototype with complete Software and original electronics (only the frame details were custom made).In January we revealed our creation on the world's largest Tech conference in the USA, where we got acquainted with Funded Today crowdfunding agency and decided that Indiegogo is the most suitable funding option for our project.Back home we started with a pre-launching campaign:NOW WE ARE HERE! WE ARE SUPER STOKED TO PRESENT PHOTON LIGHT MODULE SYSTEM TO ALL OF YOU!  Our team is a tight-knit tech international startup with members from the USA, Ukraine, and China.We have many types of specialists in different fields: electronics, developers, sales and marketing managers.We are a strong team of passionate engineers and designers who are experienced professional open-source hardware, industrial design, and photography. Our passion is all about creating products that help bring ideas and creativity to life.We have been working hard to make Photon LMS a reality.  We would like to express gratitude to all friends, supporters, backers and team members!  We unveiled Photon LMS to Tech World at CES 2019 in fabulous Las Vegas. It was a great event to start a campaign!This way or another, our product was among the projects that set the course of the industry over the year. Participating in CES was an amazing experience that left us in WOWs, opening up opportunities to meet numerous likeminded individuals.Although there are many other reasons why you'd end up loving CES.As of now, we are READY to HIT the market!THANKS FOR SUPPORT!         Risks and challengesAny project might encounter unexpected obstacles, and this possibility is even more likely in the case of a hardware technology project that requires manufacturing. Keeping this in mind, we have already started to tackle some of these obstacles early on in order to minimize any delays. We will focus on the software that we think to be the most crucial part of the development and keep the software development progress run parallel with our hardware manufacturing. We are fully aware that unexpected bumps in the road may raise, but our team is dedicated to doing whatever it takes to keep our promises. We will update you on our progress; we are very much looking forward to hearing feedback from our backers, daily, we are getting more and more prepared to deliver Photon LMS on your desks.Supply Chain Risk: Anything can happen during the production process, a machine or tool breaks, temperate factory power loss may occur. There is always a chance of getting the wrong parts or materials. All these factors can affect how long it takes place to produce our products.Shipping Risk: Providing global shipping and warehousing logistics risks we outsource that stuff for experts. But even in this case, there may be some unforeseen circumstances like weather conditions, port congestion and etc. If all goes according to a plan, we will be shipping Photon LMS to our backers by the end of August 2020. Please NOTE that this is our target timeframe and you should keep in mind that unforeseen delays might take place. It is an estimated date but not a guarantee. Remember we will not ship products out unless we know everything is of High-Quality! We will keep you closely updated and communicate with our backers in a totally transparent way.
